commit a13c6b0e006b633e1d4acf091b1ea6e6fb67c528
Author: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 3 07:27:44 2026 +0000

    Refactor: migrate FlutterFlow support layer to neutral core module
    
    ### Motivation
    - Remove FlutterFlow-specific pathing/branding and consolidate generated support utilities into a neutral `lib/core` module to make the codebase more idiomatic for hand-maintained Flutter code.
    - Provide clearer, app-centric names for shared utilities and widgets to ease future manual conversion from FlutterFlow-generated widgets to pure Flutter implementations.
    - Reduce coupling between generated scaffolding and app code by centralizing exports and improving import consistency across pages, components and backend code.
    
    ### Description
    - Moved the `lib/flutter_flow/` folder into `lib/core/` and renamed key files to neutral, app-centric names (for example `flutter_flow_util.dart` → `app_utils.dart`, `flutter_flow_theme.dart` → `app_theme.dart`, `flutter_flow_widgets.dart` → `app_widgets.dart`, `flutter_flow_model.dart` → `app_model.dart`, `flutter_flow_animations.dart` → `app_animations.dart`, `flutter_flow_calendar.dart` → `app_calendar.dart`).
    - Updated import/export paths across the app, including pages, components, backend schema and supabase database layers, to reference the new `/core/...` files and adjusted relative imports in the navigation serialization helpers to use `core/place.dart` and `core/uploaded_file.dart`.
    - Updated `lib/backend/schema/index.dart` and other schema/backend files to export/import `core/lat_lng.dart` where appropriate.
    - Preserved existing runtime logic and API surface (no functional refactors), only renames and import path updates to the generated support layer.
    
    ### Testing
    - Ran a repository-wide search for old `flutter_flow` import paths in `lib/` and verified they were removed from source files under `lib/` using `rg`/search checks, which succeeded.
    - Performed a local inspection of updated files to ensure imports and exports were consistently updated; no runtime behavior changes were introduced by the rename-only refactor.
    - Attempted to run `dart format` and `flutter --version` in this environment, but the Dart/Flutter CLIs are not available so `dart`/`flutter` commands could not be executed here.
